thailatex (0.3.7-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New maintainer (Closes:357871)
  * New upstream release (Closes: #344554, #351501)
    - updated fonts
    - new Loma font
    - addressed some fixes in 0.3.2-0.1 NMU
  * Acknowledged NMU, with some fixes addressed upstream
    (Closes: #318384, #338619)
  * debian/control:
    - put myself as the maintainer
    - changed standards version to 3.6.2.2
  * debian/changelog:
    - converted to UTF-8
  * debian/rules:
    - used $DESTDIR instead of $prefix when "make install". This is the way
      upstream has prepared for package building.
    - updated thai.map location changed upstream
    - removed upstream ChangLog zipping
    - changed DH_COMPAT to 4
  * debian/conffiles:
    - removed, as we moved to debhelper compat level 4
  * debian/docs:
    - removed upstream ChangeLog installation
    - added upstream NEWS
  * debian/postrm:
    - fixed shell script syntax error introduced in NMU

 -- Theppitak Karoonboonyanan <thep@linux.thai.net>  Mon, 27 Mar 2006 15:08:37 +0700

thailatex (0.3.2-0.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * NMU to fix RC bug: closes: #318384
  * Fix upstream Makefile to not call install-data-hook
  * Invoke updmap-sys instead of updmap, but fall back to updmap if
    updmap-sys is not found (only needed for sarge backports).
  * Update debian/babel.sty so that all new languages provided by
    teTeX-3.0 are still available when thailatex is installed.
    dpkg-diverting the file is no longer necessary, since teTeX's file is
    at a different place (closes: #338619).

